<collectingCountry box="[1044,1111,1333,1359]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="585">China</collectingCountry>
agree well with the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[233,378,1369,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Mymaridae" genus="Ooctonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lokomotiv">
<emphasis box="[233,378,1369,1396]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="585">O. lokomotiv</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Triapitsyn, S. V." box="[421,620,1369,1396]" pageId="4" pageNumber="585" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref6567" refString="Triapitsyn, S. V. (2010) Revision of the Palaearctic species and review of the Oriental species of Ooctonus (Hymenoptera: Mymaridae), with notes on extralimital taxa. Zootaxa, 2381 (1), 1 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2381.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Triapitsyn (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, which is an eastern Palearctic species. The specimens were collected in Greater Khingan Mountains, an area with temperate continental climate.
</paragraph>
